All Classes

Class Description
App
Entry point class for the application
BoardElement
The representation of an element on the board.
Direction
Represents the cardinal directions
Displayable
Represents objects that can be displayed (rendered)
ElementEditor
Represents objects that can provide and add BoardElements to itself
GameStatus
This enum represents the different status of the game
HasImage
Represents objects that have an image (ImageIcon)
HasOperator
The HAS operator When an element of the left type disappear, it is replaced by an element of the right type
IsOperator
The IS operator If the right type is a property, the elements of the left type receive said property.
LeftOperand
Represents rule parts that can be left operands
LevelBuilder
This class only serves to create a LevelManager from a given file.
LevelManager
A class that represents and manages ONE level and can manipulate its state.
LocatedObject
Represents objects that have coordinates
Movement
This record represents a movement with 2D vector
MovementObserver
Represents objects that can observe movements of BoardElements and can try to move them
Operator
Represents rule parts that can be operators
Property
Represents objects that are property types A property knows its type and its images
Property.Boom
The BOOM property An element with BOOM will instantly disappear, along with all elements directly next to it
Property.Defeat
The DEFEAT property An element with DEFEAT will make a superimposed YOU element disappear
Property.Hot
The HOT property An element with HOT will make a superimposed MELT element disappear
Property.Melt
The MELT property An element with MELT disappears when superimposed with an element with HOT
Property.Push
The PUSH property An element with PUSH can be pushed (therefore, cannot be walked over)
Property.Sink
The SINK property An elements with SINK will make any superimposed element disappear along with itself
Property.Stop
The STOP property An element with STOP cannot be walked over
Property.Win
The WIN property An element with WIN will make the state of the level as won if superimposed with a YOU element
Property.You
The YOU property An element with YOU can be controlled by the player, will disappear if superimposed with a DEFEAT element, and will make the state of the level as won if superimposed with a WIN element
PropertyChecker
Represents objects that can check if they have a property.
RightOperand
Represents rule parts that can be right operands
RightOperandType
Represents the different types of right operands ordered by priority of application
Rule
This record represents a rule, with a left operand, operator and right operand
RuleManager
This class manages the rules of a level by updating them and applying them.
RulePart
Represents a rule part
Type
This record represents the type of an element (in both its text and item version) A Type knows both its images
